helpdesk-note.body: Dear Tara-Joanne, Thank you for contacting MSOE-IT, and for sharing this email with us. As always, we thank you for your diligence in email security, and for bringing the message to our attention. It is only with the diligence and collaboration of users like yourself that we are able to maintain a secure network and secure email system for all of our students, staff, faculty, professors, and guests. We have evaluated the message you forwarded to us, it's contents, the sender, and other provided information, and we have determined that the email not in fact spam. I have personally taken a class with Dr. Farrel, and she lists both her Gmail and her outlook on her syllabus as a place to send assignments, as such, she has an autoresponder set for both so student's know when an assignment is received. This is an automatic rule, and has no way to differentiate between senders. As such, I will be resolving this ticket. If you have any further questionable messages or need to get in contact with us, please feel free to send them to helpdesk@msoe.edu, or give us a call at 414-277-7288. For your reference, this message is in regard to ticket INC-38712, https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/public/tickets/f055638bb9a287bf238838ea5869b542b87b639a04cf26651d519ac80958ad47.
